00031  SUBROUTINE Init
00032 
00033 ! Common Variables
00034  USE NTypes,    ONLY : DBL
00035  USE Domain,    ONLY : inv12, iStep, ni, NX, NY, tCall, xmax, xmin, ymax, ymin
00036  USE FluidParams
00037  USE LBMParams
00038  IMPLICIT NONE
00039 
00040 ! Local Variables
00041  INTEGER :: i, j, m, ie, iw, jn, js
00042  REAL(KIND = DBL) :: R, rhon, lapRho
00043 
00044 ! Initialize counters
00045  iStep = 0
00046  tCall = 1
00047  eps   = 1.D0
00048 
00049 ! Set vtk limits
00050  NX = xmax - xmin + 1
00051  NY = ymax - ymin + 1
00052 
00053 !-------- Define near neighbours and initialize the density rho ----------------
00054  DO j = ymin, ymax
00055    DO i = xmin, xmax
00056 
00057 ! Initialize density
00058       rho(i,j) = rhoH
00059       DO m = 1, nBubbles
00060         R =  DSQRT( ( DBLE(i)-bubbles(m,1) )**2 + ( DBLE(j)-bubbles(m,2) )**2 )
00061         IF (R <= (DBLE(bubbles(m,3)) + IntWidth)) THEN
00062           rho(i,j) = rhoStar - 0.5*(rhoH - rhoL)*TANH(2.D0*(DBLE(bubbles(m,3)) - R)/IntWidth)
00063         END IF
00064       END DO
00065 
00066 ! Generate neighbors array
00067       ni(i,j,1) = i + 1
00068       ni(i,j,2) = j + 1
00069       ni(i,j,3) = i - 1
00070       ni(i,j,4) = j - 1
00071    END DO
00072  END DO
00073 
00074 ! Fix neighbours at edges
00075  ni(xmin,:,3) = xmax
00076  ni(xmax,:,1) = xmin
00077  ni(:,ymin,4) = ymax
00078  ni(:,ymax,2) = ymin
00079 
00080 
00081 !---------- Set equilibrium distributions, pressure and velocity ---------------
00082  DO j = ymin, ymax
00083    DO i = xmin, xmax
00084 
00085 ! Define velocity and pressure
00086      rhon = rho(i,j)
00087      u(i,j,1) = 0.D0
00088      u(i,j,2) = 0.D0
00089      p(i,j)   = 1.D0
00090 
00091 ! Equilibrium values of Gamma, and the phase and pressure distributions
00092      f(i,j,0)   = W0*rhon
00093      f(i,j,1:4) = W1*rhon
00094      f(i,j,5:8) = W2*rhon
00095 
00096      g(i,j,0)   = W0C
00097      g(i,j,1:4) = W1C
00098      g(i,j,5:8) = W2C
00099 
00100    END DO
00101  END DO
00102 
00103 !--------- Differential terms for the stress form of the interfacial force -----
00104  DO j = ymin, ymax
00105    DO i = xmin, xmax
00106 
00107 ! Identify neighbors
00108      ie = ni(i,j,1)
00109      jn = ni(i,j,2)
00110      iw = ni(i,j,3)
00111      js = ni(i,j,4)
00112 
00113 ! Gradient of the density rho
00114      gradRhoX(i,j) = ( 4.D0*( rho(ie,j ) - rho(iw,j ) ) + rho(ie,jn) &
00115                    - rho(iw,js) + rho(ie,js) - rho(iw,jn) )*inv12
00116 
00117      gradRhoY(i,j) = ( 4.D0*( rho(i ,jn) - rho(i ,js) ) + rho(ie,jn) &
00118                    - rho(iw,js) + rho(iw,jn) - rho(ie,js) )*inv12
00119 
00120 ! Square of the density gradient (components and full)
00121      gradRhoXX(i,j) = gradRhoX(i,j)*gradRhoX(i,j)
00122      gradRhoXY(i,j) = gradRhoX(i,j)*gradRhoY(i,j)
00123      gradRhoYY(i,j) = gradRhoY(i,j)*gradRhoY(i,j)
00124      gradRhoSq(i,j) = gradRhoXX(i,j) + gradRhoYY(i,j)
00125 
00126 ! Laplacian of the density rho
00127      lapRho = 4.D0*( rho(ie,j ) + rho(iw,j ) + rho(i ,jn) + rho(i ,js) )       &
00128             + rho(ie,jn) + rho(ie,js) + rho(iw,jn) + rho(iw,js) - 20.D0*rho(i,j)
00129 
00130 ! Define the chemical potential Psi
00131      psi(i,j) = beta4*( rho(i,j) - rhoStar )*( rho(i,j) - rhoL )*( rho(i,j) - rhoH ) &
00132               - kappa_6*lapRho
00133    END DO
00134  END DO
00135 
00136 ! Save initialized data to file
00137  CALL Stats
00138  CALL VtkPlane
00139 
00140  RETURN
00141  END SUBROUTINE Init
